  "text": "The datasource plugin query path in grafana/grafana follows this chain: (1) HTTP request handler: `pkg/api/ds_query.go` receives POST /ds/query via `QueryMetricsV2`, which calls the query service. (2) Query orchestration: `pkg/services/query/query.go` (`ServiceImpl.queryData`) parses the metric request, determines whether it's a single-datasource, multi-datasource, or expression query, then dispatches. For single datasources it calls `handleQuerySingleDatasource` which invokes `pluginClient.QueryData`. For expressions, it calls `handleExpressions` -> `expr.Service.TransformData`. (3) Plugin client dispatch: `pkg/services/pluginsintegration/pluginsintegration.go` constructs the middleware chain wrapping `pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go` (the actual `Service.QueryData` that resolves the plugin from registry and delegates). The Plugin struct in `pkg/plugins/plugins.go` dispatches to the backend plugin implementation - either `pkg/plugins/backendplugin/coreplugin/core_plugin.go` (in-process core plugins) or `pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go` (external gRPC plugins). `pkg/plugins/ifaces.go` defines the `Client` interface. (4) Expression/transform pipeline: `pkg/expr/transform.go` (`TransformData`) builds and executes a DAG pipeline via `pkg/expr/service.go` (`BuildPipeline`/`ExecutePipeline`). `pkg/expr/nodes.go` contains `DSNode` and `executeDSNodesGrouped` which batch datasource queries and call back to the plugin client. (5) Query conversion: `pkg/expr/query_convert.go` converts backend requests to k8s-style data requests. (6) Alternative API paths: `pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go` (`QueryDataHandler`) handles the aggregator API server query endpoint, and `pkg/registry/apis/datasource/queryconvert.go` handles k8s-style query conversion via plugin conversion handlers.",
